{
  "local_port": 39110,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "Registering your mobile number with your Universal Account Number (UAN) is essential for receiving timely updates and SMS alerts related to your Employees' Provident Fund (EPF) account. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you register or update your mobile number with your UAN:\n\n### **Method 1: Through the EPFO Member Portal**\n\n1. **Visit the EPFO Unified Member Portal:**\n   - Navigate to [https://unifiedportal.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/](https://unifiedportal.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/).\n\n2. **Login to Your Account:**\n   - **User ID:** Enter your UAN.\n   - **Password:** Enter your current password. If you\u2019re logging in for the first time, use the temporary password received via SMS or from your employer.\n   - **Captcha Code:** Enter the characters shown in the image.\n   - Click on the **\"Sign In\"** button.\n\n3. **Navigate to the 'Manage' Section:**\n   - Once logged in, find and click on the **\"Manage\"** tab located on the top menu.\n\n4. **Select 'Contact Details':**\n   - Under the \"Manage\" section, click on **\"Contact Details\"**.\n\n5. **Update Mobile Number:**\n   - In the Contact Details section, you\u2019ll see fields for your mobile number and email address.\n   - Enter your **new mobile number** in the designated field.\n\n6. **Verify and Save Changes:**\n   - After entering the new number, an **OTP (One-Time Password)** will be sent to the new mobile number for verification.\n   - Enter the OTP in the provided field to verify.\n   - Click on **\"Verify\"** to confirm the changes.\n   - Once verified, ensure you **save** the updated details.\n\n7. **Confirmation:**\n   - You should receive an SMS confirming that your mobile number has been successfully updated in the EPF system.\n\n### **Method 2: Using the UMANG Mobile App**\n\nThe Universal Mobile Application for New-age Governance (UMANG) app allows you to manage various government services, including EPF details.\n\n1. **Download and Install UMANG:**\n   - Available on both [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.etebase.umang&hl=en_IN&gl=US) and [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/in/app/umang/id1422639041).\n\n2. **Register/Login:**\n   - Open the app and register using your mobile number.\n   - Verify your number with the OTP sent.\n\n3. **Access EPFO Services:**\n   - In the app, search for **\"EPF\"** or **\"Provident Fund\"** services.\n   - Select **\"Register Mobile Number\"** or a similar option.\n\n4. **Enter Required Details:**\n   - Input your UAN, member ID, and other necessary details as prompted.\n\n5. **Verification:**\n   - An OTP will be sent to your new mobile number. Enter this OTP to verify.\n\n6. **Completion:**\n   - After successful verification, your mobile number will be linked to your UAN.\n\n### **Method 3: Contacting Your Employer or EPFO Office**\n\nIf you're facing issues updating your mobile number online, you can approach your company's HR or the nearest EPFO office for assistance.\n\n1. **Through Your Employer:**\n   - Inform your HR department about the need to update your mobile number.\n   - Provide your new number and any required documentation.\n   - HR can update your details through the employer interface on the EPFO portal.\n\n2. **Visiting the EPFO Office:**\n   - Locate your nearest EPFO Regional Office.\n   - Carry identification documents such as Aadhaar, PAN, and your EPF card.\n   - Fill out the **EPF Member Details Update Form** to submit your new mobile number.\n\n### **Important Points to Consider**\n\n- **Active UAN:** Ensure your UAN is activated. You can activate it on the EPFO portal if not done already.\n  \n- **KYC Details Updated:** It's beneficial to have your KYC details (Aadhaar, PAN, bank account) updated and verified in the EPFO system for seamless service access.\n  \n- **Multiple Employers:** If you\u2019ve worked with multiple employers, ensure all details are updated across all records linked to your UAN.\n\n- **Password Issues:** If you\u2019ve forgotten your password, use the **\"Forgot Password\"** option on the EPFO portal to reset it using your registered mobile number and email.\n\n- **Help and Support:** For persistent issues, contact the EPFO helpdesk:\n  - **EPFO Helpdesk Number:** 1800 118 005\n  - **Email:** [use their official email from EPFO website]\n  - **Online Enquiry:** Available on the EPFO portal under the **\"Contact Us\"** section.\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully register or update your mobile number with your UAN, ensuring you stay informed about your EPF account activities.",
